items.name: Prometheus
items.description:
First, please take the time to watch the video, you wont regret it.

I am proud to introduce to you an innovative workflow solution for all of your prompting needs! Prometheus is a custom model along with 30 Hypernetworks I like to call Latent Later Cameras. These are virtual cameras that have been embedded in to the latent space which allow you to choose the camera angle and camera shot for your subject. These cameras put you in to the directors seat so that you always get the shot you envisioned in your mind. Besides being very flexible, the latent cameras also tend to be very cohesive and produce very good results through natural language prompting. That means there is no need for a word salad in your positive or negative prompts. In fact you can use the Hypernetworks without any negative prompts at all and still get very good results. As long as you follow very basic rules outlined in the video guide, on average you will get very good results. Thank you!

Camera shot and angle cheat sheet. https://postimg.cc/gallery/V645cMS

Huggingface link. https://huggingface.co/doctorderp/prometheus.safetensors/resolve/main/prometheus.zip

Please note the Hypernetworks work with all models...that are based on the 1.5 architecture... sorry if I misled in the video. Sorry no 2.0 or 2.1 support.

Don't forget to enable your dynamic prompts by checking the enable box, otherwise you can load the Hypernetworks manually, just know that the strength of the Hypernetworks should be at 0.55 by default, otherwise you will not get good results.

[Tip Jar](https://www.paypal.com/donate/?business=9B4V7D6BBUNPL&no_recurring=0&currency_code=USD)

Discord if you have any questions = dr.derp#7202 or just dr.derp

Hello First time uploading a LoRA (ive made a few before this is my first time uploading) So a bit of backstory behind this model, I was watching Filian and Snuffy's first VR Chat colab vod and thought to my self "Damn love snuffys model let me check if there is art of it" and i didnt find ANY art based on this model... So i desided to take it into my own hands and create this LoRA for you fine folks!

NOTICE

This LoRA ain't perfect and ONLY has training data from that 1 stream (with 37 hand picked screenshots) so its quite limited what the LoRA can do... I haven't test NSFW but i'd guess it would work...

Due to only being trained on 1 stream and no fan-art the LoRA HEAVILY enforces a VR Chat 3d model style if you like that keep the strength around 0.7 - 0.9 if you'd like to control the style a bit more id say go for 0.5 - 0.6

Refer to the trigger words to fine tune the outfit!

With that being said I hope you enjoy this model and get good use out off it and I hope to make more in the future!

items.name: Rathalos Armor (Blademaster)
items.description:
Trained on fluffyrock-576-704-832-960-1088-lion-low-lr-e83-offset-noise-e68, tested on Yiffymix 3.1.

Will likely not work on non-furry models, but you can try! It's honestly not perfect, but I consider it solid.
Both male and female sets are possible, but females generate better as they had more data.
Male helmets are imperfect, but fairly close - if you have face/eye positives it tends to give the male helmets an open face.

Two sets were trained, tagged "rathoriginal" and "rathalternate". Original refers to the blademaster set from MHFU (and the other games which share the design) while the Alternate tag refers to the more popular design that debuted in MH3. For both male and female sets, the "alternate" set has more data and tends to influence the other set slightly.

The "rathalos armor" tag can be prepended with red or azure to influence their coloration. For males, azure is more biased toward the "original" set as it had more data.
Silver was technically included, but has negligable effect from low data.

The "original" female set will often have the visor from the alternate set generate with it.

Recommended positives: red/azure/silver* rathalos armor, helmet, rathalternate**, rathoriginal**
*Defaults to red if not used, otherwise as desired.
**As desired.

Recommended negatives: boob window*, red hair*, visor**
*For females. Red hair will sometimes turn into the helmet, turning the visor into more of a headpiece. Neat, but not intended.
**When generating female "original" armor, high weight helps.

items.name: Tanishi (hentai model)
items.description:
A model with Tanishi artstyle in mind. There is already a Lora if you want that (here). The Lora is not made by me. Trained on AnyHentai as base model.

What does Tanishi style add:

-Pubic hair added easily (anus,vagina) in images
-Tanish arstyle armpit hair added automatically if there is armpit in the image

-Easier to obtain Thick,plump, big breasts, saggy breasts images

-Clothes are tight even if I don't prompt that

-Super black skin(12.5% chance to get one image like that)

-Easier to obtain black and white images compared to other hentai models


Negative prompt: (speech bubble:1.3),(text:1.3),(logo:1.3),(signature:1.3)

Important to read for Negative prompt
You might want to add in certain images/seeds negative prompts such as: (pussy juice) or (naked) or use weight like (naked:1.3). I use Low cfg scale so I say this because It tend to generate so NSFW in certain cases, that you actually don't want that, so for low cfg scale numbers, add strong negative prompt to avoid that.

Full Negative prompt: easynegative, badhandv4, lr, beard, curly, veiny, muscular, ((bodybuilder)), facial hair, mustache, lowres, fewer fingers, out of frame, jpeg artifacts, ugly, duplicate, morbid,mutilated, extra fingers, mutated hands, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn face, mutation, deformed, blurry, dehydrated, bad anatomy, bad proportions, extra limbs, cloned face, disfigured, gross proportions, malformed limbs, missing arms, missing legs, extra arms, extra legs, fused fingers,(speech bubble:1.3),(text:1.3),(logo:1.3),(signature:1.3)


Settings
It should work with your usual settings but here are mine:

  • Sampler: Euler a (is what I use but works with others as well from what I saw)

  • Size: 512-512 / 512-744 (didn't tried with 512-768, but I assume it works)

  • Clip skip: 2 (seems clip skip1 images are ok? I guess, but I main "2")

  • Sampling Steps: 20-30 (I use 30 all the time)

  • Hiresfix upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x Anime6B on 2x, steps: 20, denoise 0.5 (I didn't test higher or lower than 0.5).

  • Cfg scale: 6-7 (didn't tried higher or lower)


Why make a model if there is a Lora already? (#rant)
- Because I find Lora to be very stiff, yes Lora are great, and I use them all the time. But I wanted to make "black skin" or "black and white" images. Can the lora do that? yeah... It kinda struggle to do that. And I think it's because it mainly had only white girls in training. If there is a booru tag that get that specific thing I want, I am too lazy to find that specific tag, to activate Lora's potential. ('why don't use multiple Lora to get what you want', what if I want 100 unique things, that require 100 unique Lora, if a model can do those 100 things, i'd rather spend the time to make a model than spending the time to get all the Lora I want)

You said earlier it's important to read that text for negative prompt but wasn't important tho?
- Yeah I understand that 90% of people here already know to use models, I wrote that in case people copy me and use my cfg scale and they get half naked model even if they wrote: jeans,shirt,fully clothed. I know that higher cfg scale should in theory fix this issue, But I usually enjoy when I let the model be the artist and surprise me, so I still want that randomness and not complying to my full prompt, but at the same time avoid certain elements, so the weight in negative prompt should fix that

How Many Images I used for training?
- 166, And I edited around 10. I don't use mask to get a character out of an image, I like to get the background as well, I feel like if the character get pulled only, then the background will get added by whatever model I train mine on, and I don't want that type background (janky girl with realistic background for e.g). Plus there is always merging if people want same artstyle and improve stuff such as Background or body,etc.
